raw_data.title: Engineering Technician
raw_data.description: The ETech is responsible for prototype fabrication and manufacturing.  The position will be required to work with our existing engineers, assemblers and outside suppliers to facilitate internal prototype projects.  Responsibilities include machining, fabricating, electrical component assembly and some design.

raw_data.title: Engineering Analyst
raw_data.description: The MSI EA has a range of responsibilities including but not limited to the development of spreadsheets, projection tools, and tracking tools for MSI projects.  An example would be a tracking and planning worksheet for a prototype development project, managing lead times, cash flow outlays for prototype parts, and ensuring that the components to build prototypes and production builds are properly planned for and tracked.  The EA will also interface with the MSI Purchasing Dept and Finance Dept to accurately track costs for accumulation into Request for Proposal (RFP) submissions, costing analyses, and into production cost analyses.

raw_data.title: Design Engineer
raw_data.description: The Design Engineer will work under the President/Technical Director in our Mooresville, NC facility.  The Design Engineer is responsible for the modeling, design, and analysis of the mechanical components with the majority of the work being damper design.  The position will be required to work with our existing engineers, assemblers and suppliers to facilitate internal and outside manufacturing.  Responsibilities include design changes involving Finite Element Analysis based on information provided by customers, other MSI engineers or calculations.

raw_data.title: Assembler
raw_data.description: Experience in mechanical assembly of components, including but not limited to vehicle sub systems such as engine and drivetrain components, brake systems, sterring systems, exhaust systems, hydraulic systems, cooling systems, suspension systems. Experience in basic mechanical assembly techniques, application of thread lockers, safety wire, use of torque wrenches and appropriate torque specifications for fasteners.  Ability to take instruction from the Vehicle Team leader and Production Manager.

raw_data.title: Fabricator
raw_data.description: Experience in Welding, including but not limited to Mig, Heli-Arc, and gas welding, various materials including but not limited to mild Steel, Chrome moly, aluminum alloys. Welds will be tested by an outside lab for quality.  Experience in Material Shaping, use of material breaks, shears, Rotex punches, notcher, horizontal and vertical band saw, various hand tools for material shaping and grinding.

raw_data.title: Quality Control Tehcnician
raw_data.description: The QC Tech will take direction with regards to scheduling and immediate need from the Parts Procurement Manager and Shop Production Manager.  The position is responsible for ensuring company’s quality standards for all parts and processes.  The position will be required to work with our design staff, Parts Manager and Production Manager as well as outside suppliers to address and correct any shortcomings in sourcing, manufacturing or assembly.  A computer will be provided as well as any necessary training on inventory and accounting software.

raw_data.title: Senior Assembler
raw_data.description: Take instruction from the Vehicle Team leader and Production Manager.  Ability to carry out assigned tasks unassisted or with little assistance with accuracy.  Ability to operate a computer and understand the Shop Floor Manager software implemented by the Company, and to adhere to the discipline of the systems use per the instruction from management.

raw_data.title: Program Manager
raw_data.description: The Program Manager will manage and provide overall leadership and guidance to Projects including Development, Production and Service.  The Program Manager will be responsible for on-going project success as well as growth in the revenue of the Company by creating efficient and effective practices.  Ensure all contractual requirements are met.

raw_data.title: Inventory Technician
raw_data.description: Familiarity with automotive and mechanical parts.  Receiving incoming inventory.  Pulling components for new orders from Sales Order Picking Lists accurately and on time.  Delivery of parts to the Production Floor.

raw_data.title: Inventory Clerk/Drive
raw_data.description: The Shipping & Receiving clerk position verifies and keeps records on incoming and outgoing shipments and prepares items for shipment by performing the following duties to quality and productivity standards. Operates lift trucks or hand trucks to convey, move or hoist materials to proper departments or areas. Clerk will also be responsible for delivering materials to vendors or picking up products from vendors.

raw_data.title: Admin Support
raw_data.description: Performs full administrative, and broad support activities of a highly responsible and confidential nature for MSI Engineering Department. This position serves in a critical support role, primarily to the personnel within the Department, but also to the Director of Engineering.  This position requires significant interface on a regular basis with high level executives within the company, governmental and regulatory officials or officers of other companies.

raw_data.title: Deputy Program Manager
raw_data.description: The Deputy Program Manager will support the Program Manager by providing oversight, leadership and guidance to Projects including Development, Production and Service.  The Deputy Program Manager will be responsible for on-going project success as well as growth in the revenue of the Company by creating efficient and effective practices.

raw_data.title: Facility Security Officer
raw_data.description: Manage all aspects of NISPOM-compliant DoD program security, including security procedures, protocols and compliance.  Manage and facilitate Security Clearance requirements per NISPOM and other Customer requirements as appropriate.  Perpare and participate in Defense Security Service (DSS) audits.  Perform self-inspections as required.  Investigate, prepare, and submit Security Violations and Incident Reports as required by NISPOM.  Conduct security trainings, briefings, and debriefings.  Maintain records, databases, and forms for security documentation.

raw_data.title: Fabrication Lead
raw_data.description: Coordinate, manage, and monitor schedules and the performance of the warehouse team.  Plan production schedule as required and ensure it is being maintained to meet on time shipment of orders based on customer expectations.  Perform in process and final inspection on orders going through the shop to maintain quality standards that meet customer expectations.  Prepare and process all paperwork necessary to complete orders.

raw_data.title: Electrical Technician
raw_data.description: Experience in electrical wiring, circuit design, knowledge of assembly techniques of wiring looms and electrical assemblies. A good working knowledge of electrical circuits for the purposes of trouble shooting and diagnosis of electrical issues.  Knowledge of electrical symbols and the reading of circuit diagrams.

raw_data.title: Electrical Engineer
raw_data.description: The Electrical Engineer has a range of responsibilities including controls systems design, specification, programming, simulation and testing as well as electrical design and mechanical systems integration. The goal of the position is to develop an in-house capability to design, develop, test, and deliver in prototype and production quantities electrical, electronic, and controls level projects for our Customers.

raw_data.title: Manufacturing Manager
raw_data.description: The Manufacturing Manager oversees management of all areas of manufacturing to produce products and direct activities so that approved products are manufactured on schedule and within quality standards and cost objectives.  Formulates and recommends manufacturing policies and programs that guide the organization in maintaining and improving its competitive position and the profitability of the operation.

raw_data.title: Project Coordinator
raw_data.description: Project Coordinator responsibilities include but are not limited to working closely with Project Engineers, Purchasing, Inventory, Quality, Production, and Shipping Departments to prepare comprehensive action plans, including resources, timeframes and budgets for projects.  To succeed in this role, you should have excellent time management and communication skills as you’ll collaborate with internal teams to deliver results on time.  Ultimately, the Project Coordinator’s duties are to ensure that all projects are completed on time, within budget, and meet high quality standards.   The Project Coordinator will report to the Director of Operations.
